JOHANNESBURG – World champion, Caster Semenya cruised into the finals of the 1500m race to claim gold for South Africa. Semenya set the Commonwealth Games record in 4:00.71 as well as SA's national record. READ: Caster Semenya using SA Champs as race prep for international season She finished ahead of Kenya's Beatrice Chepkoech, who took silver. Wales' Melissa Courtney took the bronze. Her win brings SA's medal tally to 21 -- 9 gold medals, 6 silver and 6 bronze medals respectively. Meanwhile, South Africa is ranked 5th in the medal standings. eNCA